narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you took Russian 130, you can expect the same thing in 140. There is nightly homework as well as quizzes/tests for each unit. You do more reading of Russian literature in 140, but it's essentially a continuation of 130. I really enjoyed it and would definitely recommend it!

I would recommend this class if you are continuing from lower level at Yale. It is a decent amount of daily work (well, depends how seriously you take it - i definitely recommend trying to check it by googling), so not a class you can cram for right before exams.

2nd year Russian is extremely well taught and is as engaging as any language class I've taken at Yale. It is still a language, and a fairly tricky on at that, so there's plenty of memorization and that sort of thing, but the class is taught extremely well.

I would not recommend 140 to a student coming in with the same Russian background as I had coming in. I would recommend something higher. Some specific details of constructions and grammar things got clearer for me this year, but there wasn't really any new material.
I would absolutely recommend taking Russian with Irina. She is one of the best Russian instructors I've ever had (probably the best, actually).
